Let me implement:

1. Add `--trajectory-file` argument (optional Path)
2. After line 2297 (assessment is read), add logic to augment with trajectory gnomes

Here's the augmentation logic:
```python
if args.trajectory_file and args.trajectory_file.exists() and \
   args.assessment.name == "assessment_missing.md":
    try:
        traj_text = args.trajectory_file.read_text(encoding="utf-8", errors="replace")
        traj_gnomes = numeric_metrics(traj_text)
        # Only augment if trajectory has gnomes not already in assessment
        assess_gnomes = numeric_metrics(assessment)
        missing_gnomes = {k: v for k, v in traj_gnomes.items() 
                         if k not in assess_gnomes}
        if missing_gnomes:
            gnome_lines = "\n".join(f"{k}={v}" for k, v in missing_gnomes.items())
            assessment = f"## Trajectory Gnomes (from trajectory.md)\n{gnome_lines}\n\n{assessment}"
    except OSError:
        pass
```

This way, the existing `numeric_metrics(assessment)` call at line 1042 will pick up the trajectory gnomes, and all the existing logic at lines 1041-1096 will work unchanged.

